  "body": "Hi there, I saw this \"Users need to make sure their validator doesn't have downtime or they risk a quadratic leak on their stake.â€œ  Is there a way for validator to suspend service due to maintenance ? Otherwise it is quite unfair to validator who want to switch server or do maintenance job. So during the suspension period, they won't get reward.\r\n\r\nThe original proposal would scare off lots of ordinary people who want to join validators team, which requires redundant validator client.  People using their own computer to validate may encounter power off, computer upgrade. This will happen even if people use aws. \r\n\r\n",
