    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "In normal chain finality conditions, having ~50-60% uptime keeps a validator in the black. Being about to suspend validation introduces significant consensus complexity and the validator would still be subject to activation/exit queues/times. \r\n\r\nOnce validator Transfers are added, the normal flow for suspending would be to exit, then to later Transfer eth to a new validator account for new activation.",
